description: System-generated unique identifier for the warehouse record.
Last update timestamp for this record, likely UTC with millisecond precision; used for auditing and synchronization.
Mobile phone number for the warehouse’s primary contact.
Fax number for the warehouse or site office.
Alternate phone number for the warehouse (secondary line or after-hours).
Primary phone number for the warehouse.
Postal/ZIP code for the warehouse’s physical address.
City of the warehouse’s physical address.
Second address line (suite, building, unit, etc.).
Street address of the warehouse.
Last name of the warehouse’s primary contact.
First name of the warehouse’s primary contact.
Internal location identifier or description for the warehouse (e.g., site code or GPS); meaning may vary by client; confirm with SME.
Official name of the warehouse.
Name of the company or business unit operating/owning the warehouse; confirm with SME.
Free-text notes or special instructions related to the warehouse.
Email address for the warehouse or primary contact.
General ledger or cost account code used to charge repair/maintenance transactions for this warehouse.
Human-readable description/name corresponding to the repairs_account code.
State or province code/ID for the warehouse’s address; format may be code or reference key; confirm with SME.
Human-readable state/province name corresponding to state.
Organizational hierarchy level 1 identifier for this warehouse (e.g., region/division).
Display name or description for hierlvl1.
Website URL for the warehouse or operating company.
Identifier for this warehouse in a legacy/source system to support data migration or cross-references.
Name of the legacy/source table associated with legacykey.
Indicates whether the warehouse is inactive or decommissioned.
Indicates a mobile or rolling warehouse (inventory carried on a vehicle).
Indicates this warehouse maintains stocked spare parts inventory.
Source or replenishment warehouse identifier from which this warehouse receives stock; confirm with SME.
Human-readable name/description of the source warehouse referenced by srcwhs.
Indicator or reference linking this warehouse to an equipment depot/group or equipment capability; confirm with SME.
Human-readable description for equip.
Organizational hierarchy level 9 identifier used for deep grouping/rollups; usage varies by client; confirm with SME.
Display name or description for hierlvl9.
Organizational hierarchy level 2 identifier (e.g., district/area) for this warehouse.
Display name or description for hierlvl2.
